        "content": "<p><code>simp</code> solves this. And this makes sense: statements like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IntermediateField.fixingSubgroup_bot#doc\">docs#IntermediateField.fixingSubgroup_bot</a> are very natural <code>simp</code> lemmas because the RHS is unambiguously simpler than the LHS.</p>",
